  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6772.57 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6770 (-9293.7M) and max positive gamma at 6780 (+10173.8M), dealers are currently in buy-mode as spot trades below the flip at 6796, providing modest support here. The PIN regime combined with this tight 10-point gamma sandwich creates a strong mean-reversion setup, with dealers expected to aggressively buy any dip toward 6770 and sell any push toward 6780. The gex_surge event and massive -40.1% five-minute GEX decline suggests we're seeing rapid options flow that's compressing the trading range even tighter around these critical 6770/6780 boundaries.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect choppy, range-bound action between 6770-6780 with limited breakout potential.",
